.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH rom-weaver-extract 1  "rom-weaver-extract "
.SH NAME
rom\-weaver\-extract \- Extract files and disc payloads from supported containers
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrom\-weaver extract\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-select\fR] [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-rom\-filter\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-filter\fR] <\fB\-\-out\-dir\fR> [\fB\-\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-split\-bin\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-nested\-extract\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-overwrite\fR] [\fB\-\-checksum\fR] [\fB\-\-checksum\-rom\fR] [\fB\-\-probe\fR] [\fB\-\-threads\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fISOURCE\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Extract files and disc payloads from supported containers
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit progress and terminal status as JSON lines
.TP
\fB\-\-select\fR \fI<SELECT>\fR
Select extracted entries by exact name, prefix, or glob (repeatable). Examples: \-\-select game.disc02.cue \-\-select \*(Aqgame.disc0?.bin\*(Aq
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR
Force running progress events on
.TP
\fB\-\-rom\-filter\fR
Extract ROM\-like entries and nested containers only
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable running progress events
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-filter\fR
Extract patch\-like entries and nested containers only
.TP
\fB\-\-out\-dir\fR \fI<DIR>\fR
Directory for extracted files
.TP
\fB\-\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs (also enabled by ROM_WEAVER_LOG or RUST_LOG)
.TP
\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs from dependencies (for example nod)
.TP
\fB\-\-split\-bin\fR
For CHD CD extraction, force split CUE + per\-track BIN output (`*.trackNN.bin`) instead of a single BIN when possible
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR
Disable default common\-file ignore filtering during container extraction
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-nested\-extract\fR
Do not recursively extract nested containers emitted by this extraction
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-overwrite\fR
Fail extraction if any destination output file already exists
.TP
\fB\-\-checksum\fR \fI<ALGO>\fR
Compute an output checksum while extracting; repeat for multiple algorithms
.TP
\fB\-\-checksum\-rom\fR \fI<ALGO>\fR
Like \-\-checksum but only ROM\-like outputs are hashed (sidecar/non\-ROM entries are skipped); safe to always pass. Ignored if \-\-checksum is also set
.TP
\fB\-\-probe\fR
Fold container/platform probe metadata into the result and fail when a single\-payload source resolves to no known platform
.TP
\fB\-\-threads\fR \fI<auto|N>\fR [default: auto]
Thread budget: auto or a positive integer
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fISOURCE\fR>
Container or disc image to extract
